1
00:00:00,601 --> 00:00:02,036
Ikalgo: All I know is this--

2
00:00:02,069 --> 00:00:05,573
you looked at a good-for-nothing
octopus like me,

3
00:00:05,606 --> 00:00:07,575
and you said I was cool.

4
00:00:07,608 --> 00:00:10,611
you even said
we could have been friends.

5
00:00:11,745 --> 00:00:14,214
I can’t stand by while you die!

6
00:00:18,685 --> 00:00:23,557
I’m gonna save you!
Don’t you die on me!

7
00:00:23,590 --> 00:00:24,558
♪

8
00:00:24,591 --> 00:00:26,593
( Singing in Japanese )

9
00:01:08,001 --> 00:01:10,003
♪

10
00:01:15,342 --> 00:01:17,778
Narrator: While killua
was in the process

11
00:01:17,811 --> 00:01:20,314
of being rescued
by the chimera ant ikalgo,

12
00:01:20,347 --> 00:01:23,016
a creature he had thought
was his enemy,

13
00:01:23,050 --> 00:01:25,386
gon was forming a bond as well

14
00:01:25,419 --> 00:01:29,123
with a chimera ant
who goes by the name meleoron.

15
00:01:29,156 --> 00:01:30,924
( Lighter flicks )

16
00:01:36,864 --> 00:01:39,400
Gon: You should really
stop smoking, you know.

17
00:01:39,433 --> 00:01:40,834
Meleoron: Huh?

18
00:01:40,868 --> 00:01:42,837
gon: The smoke
will stick to your clothes,

19
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:44,238
and people
will smell you coming,

20
00:01:44,271 --> 00:01:45,873
which kind of defeats
the purpose

21
00:01:45,906 --> 00:01:47,307
of you being invisible,
doesn’t it?

22
00:01:47,341 --> 00:01:50,344
( Meleoron laughs )
I appreciate the tip,

23
00:01:50,377 --> 00:01:52,813
but honestly,
it doesn’t really matter much.

24
00:01:52,846 --> 00:01:56,249
while my invisibility
is sort of like my trademark,

25
00:01:56,283 --> 00:01:59,186
my real ability
goes one step further.

26
00:01:59,219 --> 00:02:00,220
Gon: What?

27
00:02:00,254 --> 00:02:02,723
Meleoron: Here. I’ll show you.

28
00:02:04,124 --> 00:02:05,425
( Inhales )

29
00:02:05,459 --> 00:02:08,829
( Gasping )

30
00:02:08,862 --> 00:02:11,898
What the--he’s gone.

31
00:02:13,066 --> 00:02:15,035
I can’t sense him at all,

32
00:02:15,068 --> 00:02:16,836
only the smell of cigarettes.

33
00:02:19,306 --> 00:02:21,041
He’s not here.

34
00:02:21,074 --> 00:02:23,043
this is more
than just invisibility.

35
00:02:23,076 --> 00:02:27,347
Does he also have the ability
to change locations instantly

36
00:02:27,381 --> 00:02:30,384
without even making a sound?

37
00:02:30,417 --> 00:02:34,087
That’s impossible,
so how did he do it?

38
00:02:34,121 --> 00:02:36,090
( Gasps ) Whoa!

39
00:02:36,123 --> 00:02:37,992
Where did you come from?

40
00:02:38,025 --> 00:02:41,328
Meleoron: Hmm? I’ve been
right here the whole time.

41
00:02:41,361 --> 00:02:43,029
( Gon gasps )

42
00:02:43,063 --> 00:02:46,166
Meleoron: My second ability
is perfect plan.

43
00:02:47,801 --> 00:02:51,071
Whenever I hold my breath,
it prevents anyone around me

44
00:02:51,104 --> 00:02:53,873
from sensing my presence,
even a little bit.

45
00:02:53,907 --> 00:02:57,711
You were touching me and didn’t
even realize you were doing it.

46
00:02:57,744 --> 00:02:59,312
Your mind simply refused
to acknowledge

47
00:02:59,346 --> 00:03:00,881
what your eyes couldn’t see.

48
00:03:00,914 --> 00:03:02,983
Gon: Huh? I really touched you?

49
00:03:04,351 --> 00:03:07,054
Meleoron: You know how
some guys never get noticed?

50
00:03:07,087 --> 00:03:10,924
Like the guy the waitress skips
over when you go out to eat

51
00:03:10,958 --> 00:03:12,993
in a big group
at a chain restaurant?

52
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:14,895
It’s like that,
but more extreme.

53
00:03:14,928 --> 00:03:18,298
i’m right here,
but no one ever notices me.

54
00:03:18,332 --> 00:03:19,900
Gon: Uh...

55
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:23,503
Meleoron: Turning invisible
really is just a decoy.

56
00:03:23,537 --> 00:03:25,973
it helps me
keep my true ability

57
00:03:26,006 --> 00:03:28,075
a secret from everyone else.

58
00:03:28,108 --> 00:03:31,078
And that’s just between
you and me, of course.

59
00:03:31,111 --> 00:03:34,181
Nobody else knows,

60
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:36,817
so let’s just keep it
that way, all right?

61
00:03:36,850 --> 00:03:37,984
( Gon gasps )

62
00:03:38,018 --> 00:03:41,188
why tell me
something so important?

63
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:44,057
Meleoron: Well, i’ve gotta earn
your trust, don’t I?

64
00:03:44,091 --> 00:03:47,294
Yeah, it’s kind of a risk,
but it’s one I have to take.

65
00:03:47,327 --> 00:03:49,896
See, if I can’t
get you to trust me,

66
00:03:49,930 --> 00:03:52,065
then we won’t be able
to start anything.

67
00:03:52,099 --> 00:03:55,469
Gon: You mean how you said i’d
be a valuable partner, right?

68
00:03:55,502 --> 00:03:56,937
Meleoron: That’s right,

69
00:03:56,970 --> 00:03:59,473
but let’s hold off on that
for right now.

70
00:03:59,506 --> 00:04:00,474
Gon: Eh?

71
00:04:00,507 --> 00:04:02,209
Meleoron: Like I said before,

72
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:04,344
we have to trust
each other first.

73
00:04:04,378 --> 00:04:06,447
Once you’ve agreed
to be my partner,

74
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:09,483
i’ll be happy to tell you
everything you want to know.

75
00:04:09,516 --> 00:04:11,385
Gon: Okay. I’ll be your partner.

76
00:04:11,418 --> 00:04:13,020
( Meleoron chuckles )
That was fast!

77
00:04:13,053 --> 00:04:15,322
you don’t know
how to negotiate, kid!

78
00:04:15,355 --> 00:04:16,923
Cut the trusting crap!

79
00:04:16,957 --> 00:04:19,560
You should be suspicious of me,
of the whole world!

80
00:04:19,593 --> 00:04:21,462
think about it
before you trust anyone!

81
00:04:21,495 --> 00:04:24,565
Gon: Huh? I said it’s fine.
Why are you being such a drag?

82
00:04:24,598 --> 00:04:26,166
Meleoron: Besides,
are you even able

83
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:27,802
to make this decision
all by yourself?!

84
00:04:27,835 --> 00:04:29,170
What about your buddy?!

85
00:04:29,203 --> 00:04:31,305
Isn’t he gonna have a fit
when he finds out

86
00:04:31,338 --> 00:04:33,941
you teamed up with
a suspicious-looking monster?!

87
00:04:33,974 --> 00:04:36,143
( Groans )

88
00:04:36,176 --> 00:04:38,879
why the hell am I
trashing myself like this?

89
00:04:38,912 --> 00:04:41,381
it’s not like
I chose to be this way.

90
00:04:41,415 --> 00:04:43,150
Gon: He sure is restless.

91
00:04:43,183 --> 00:04:44,151
( Meleoron sighs )

92
00:04:44,184 --> 00:04:45,886
I guess it doesn’t matter.

93
00:04:45,919 --> 00:04:48,822
Even a good friend
you’ve had for 20 years

94
00:04:48,856 --> 00:04:50,925
could still
stab you in the back.

95
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:52,993
Time is not a matter of trust.

96
00:04:53,026 --> 00:04:54,995
You feel me?

97
00:04:55,028 --> 00:04:56,196
( Groans )

98
00:04:56,230 --> 00:04:58,866
You’re not much fun, huh?

99
00:04:58,899 --> 00:05:00,901
We could never be friends.

100
00:05:00,934 --> 00:05:03,203
( Gon thinking )
I feel the same way.

101
00:05:04,404 --> 00:05:06,373
meleoron: Well,
are you sure about this?

102
00:05:06,406 --> 00:05:07,507
Gon: What?

103
00:05:07,541 --> 00:05:09,176
meleoron:
About teaming up with me.

104
00:05:09,209 --> 00:05:11,178
Won’t your buddy object?

105
00:05:11,211 --> 00:05:13,246
Gon: Hmm. Yeah, probably.

106
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:15,883
Killua’s pretty cautious
about everything.

107
00:05:15,916 --> 00:05:17,551
Meleoron: Then we’re done.

108
00:05:17,584 --> 00:05:20,020
This deal is dead in the water.

109
00:05:20,053 --> 00:05:21,221
Gon: Nah. It’s fine.

110
00:05:21,255 --> 00:05:23,557
I’ll just insist
on having it my way.

111
00:05:23,590 --> 00:05:26,093
Killua won’t like it,
but he’ll give in.

112
00:05:26,126 --> 00:05:28,061
Meleoron: Well, there you go.

113
00:05:28,095 --> 00:05:30,364
Kid’s got his work
cut out for him.

114
00:05:30,397 --> 00:05:34,234
Whatever. If you say it’s okay,
I trust you,

115
00:05:34,268 --> 00:05:36,370
so let’s get down to business.

116
00:05:36,403 --> 00:05:37,371
Gon: Sure.

117
00:05:37,404 --> 00:05:39,907
Meleoron: I wanna...

118
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:41,675
Take down the king.

119
00:05:43,577 --> 00:05:45,879
Wanna know why?

120
00:05:45,913 --> 00:05:47,982
Gon: Well, yeah. Of course I do.

121
00:05:48,015 --> 00:05:50,584
That’s what i’ve
been waiting for.

122
00:05:50,617 --> 00:05:53,186
Meleoron: I’m taking revenge.

123
00:05:53,220 --> 00:05:55,389
( Gon gasps )

124
00:05:55,422 --> 00:05:58,091
Meleoron: I can’t tell you
any of the details

125
00:05:58,125 --> 00:06:00,094
on why I want revenge right now.

126
00:06:00,127 --> 00:06:02,997
Gon: Okay. I’m kinda curious
about it, but I can wait.

127
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:05,599
that’s probably
what you want me to say.

128
00:06:05,632 --> 00:06:07,134
( Meleoron sighs )

129
00:06:07,167 --> 00:06:10,103
If you insist, I guess
i’ll have to tell you.

130
00:06:10,137 --> 00:06:11,105
Gon: What?! Already?!

131
00:06:11,138 --> 00:06:12,439
Meleoron: I’m just kidding.

132
00:06:12,472 --> 00:06:15,909
beg all you want,
but I won’t tell you yet.

133
00:06:15,943 --> 00:06:17,945
Gon: I didn’t beg
for anything.

134
00:06:19,279 --> 00:06:20,313
( Lighter flicks )

135
00:06:20,347 --> 00:06:22,249
( Meleoron exhales )

136
00:06:23,617 --> 00:06:27,154
The king killed
someone who saved me.

137
00:06:28,188 --> 00:06:30,057
His name was Peggy.

138
00:06:30,090 --> 00:06:33,360
I saw the king behead him
right before my eyes.

139
00:06:34,962 --> 00:06:35,930
( Gon gasps )

140
00:06:35,963 --> 00:06:37,465
Meleoron: But at the time,

141
00:06:37,498 --> 00:06:38,933
I didn’t even realize

142
00:06:38,966 --> 00:06:40,935
that someone who was
close to me had died.

143
00:06:40,968 --> 00:06:43,103
Gon: Huh? Why not?

144
00:06:43,136 --> 00:06:45,438
You just said you saw it happen.

145
00:06:50,077 --> 00:06:53,681
meleoron: Because i’d
forgotten who Peggy was to me.

146
00:06:53,714 --> 00:06:57,952
I’d forgotten that he
was my foster father.

147
00:06:57,985 --> 00:06:59,920
♪

148
00:07:02,489 --> 00:07:05,993
I remembered only recently.

149
00:07:06,026 --> 00:07:09,062
Memories of my human days
came flooding back.

150
00:07:10,531 --> 00:07:13,267
Not all of it, of course.

151
00:07:14,501 --> 00:07:17,137
Well, that’s not quite right.

152
00:07:17,171 --> 00:07:19,707
there isn’t much
that I remembered at all,

153
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:23,310
my parents’ names
and my own name,

154
00:07:23,343 --> 00:07:24,678
bits of my childhood.

155
00:07:24,711 --> 00:07:26,713
Peggy was the name

156
00:07:26,747 --> 00:07:30,084
of the chimera ant
that the king killed,

157
00:07:30,117 --> 00:07:34,455
and that was also
my foster father’s human name.

158
00:07:34,488 --> 00:07:36,991
He was an academic,

159
00:07:37,024 --> 00:07:40,060
always carrying thick books
with him everywhere.

160
00:07:43,363 --> 00:07:46,166
In his previous life,
he carried a copy

161
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,669
of the ngl Bible with him
all the time.

162
00:07:48,702 --> 00:07:52,673
Gon: Do all the ants have
human memories like you do?

163
00:07:52,706 --> 00:07:55,275
Meleoron: I don’t know
if we’re all the same.

164
00:07:55,309 --> 00:07:58,612
Some chimera ants are
obviously feral in nature,

165
00:07:58,645 --> 00:08:00,447
which makes it
virtually impossible

166
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:02,015
to tell what they’re thinking.

167
00:08:02,049 --> 00:08:03,684
Gon: Then, I think I get it now.

168
00:08:03,717 --> 00:08:05,185
Meleoron: Eh?

169
00:08:05,219 --> 00:08:08,089
I think i’m finally
starting to understand

170
00:08:08,121 --> 00:08:11,091
why I felt I could
trust you so quickly.

171
00:08:11,124 --> 00:08:13,093
It’s ’cause you seem so human,

172
00:08:13,126 --> 00:08:16,129
more human than all
the other ants i’ve met so far.

173
00:08:16,163 --> 00:08:19,600
In fact, I would even say
that you’re still a human.

174
00:08:19,633 --> 00:08:21,602
Meleoron: Really?
When I met you,

175
00:08:21,635 --> 00:08:23,604
i had exactly
the opposite reaction.

176
00:08:23,637 --> 00:08:24,738
Gon: Eh?

177
00:08:24,771 --> 00:08:26,473
Meleoron: I could
immediately sense

178
00:08:26,507 --> 00:08:28,743
an inhuman beast
lurking deep within you.

179
00:08:28,775 --> 00:08:31,745
That’s why I wanted
to team up with you,

180
00:08:31,778 --> 00:08:34,748
because we’re not all
that different, you and I.

181
00:08:37,384 --> 00:08:40,354
all right.
Let’s get right to it, then.

182
00:08:40,387 --> 00:08:44,391
But before we do that,
I should know your name.

183
00:08:44,424 --> 00:08:46,159
I just forgot to ask.

184
00:08:48,195 --> 00:08:51,598
Gon: Oh, right.
I’m gon freecss.

185
00:08:51,632 --> 00:08:54,602
Meleoron: I actually
have one more ability,

186
00:08:54,635 --> 00:08:57,605
and we just met
the condition to activate it.

187
00:08:57,638 --> 00:08:59,773
( Gon gasps )

188
00:08:59,806 --> 00:09:04,277
Meleoron: Time to show you
my third ability.

189
00:09:04,311 --> 00:09:08,081
( Gon gasps )

190
00:09:08,115 --> 00:09:10,684
♪

191
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:12,485
Meleoron: Activate!

192
00:09:19,526 --> 00:09:20,861
Huh.

193
00:09:22,830 --> 00:09:24,832
( Bird chirping )

194
00:09:40,848 --> 00:09:43,651
Gon: It isn’t flying away.

195
00:09:43,684 --> 00:09:45,619
( Meleoron exhales )

196
00:09:45,652 --> 00:09:46,820
- ( Bird tweeting )
- ( Gon gasps )

197
00:09:48,922 --> 00:09:50,457
Wait a second.

198
00:09:50,490 --> 00:09:53,626
Does that mean I was using
your perfect plan, too?

199
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:55,629
Meleoron: That’s exactly right,

200
00:09:55,662 --> 00:09:59,566
and the name of my third power
is god’s accomplice.

201
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:03,304
While perfect plan is activated,
it allows anyone else I touch

202
00:10:03,337 --> 00:10:06,307
to use it
the very same way I do.

203
00:10:06,340 --> 00:10:08,642
♪

204
00:10:08,675 --> 00:10:13,313
Now do you understand
how powerful this is?

205
00:10:13,347 --> 00:10:16,383
This ability will allow us
to approach and attack

206
00:10:16,416 --> 00:10:21,254
an unsuspecting enemy,
and they won’t see it coming.

207
00:10:21,288 --> 00:10:24,825
No matter how powerful
the king is,

208
00:10:24,858 --> 00:10:28,562
one mega-punch to his
unguarded vitals, and he’s done.

209
00:10:28,595 --> 00:10:30,931
( Gon shudders )

210
00:10:30,964 --> 00:10:32,899
Meleoron: Hey, gon,

211
00:10:32,933 --> 00:10:35,936
you’re just the perfect partner
i’ve been looking for.

212
00:10:37,571 --> 00:10:39,873
If we work together,

213
00:10:39,907 --> 00:10:43,878
we can deal that son of a bitch
an unprecedented blow.

214
00:10:51,585 --> 00:10:53,954
So I was watching you

215
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:56,890
back when you used
that jan-Ken-rock thing.

216
00:10:58,392 --> 00:11:00,895
- Those were my men, you know.
- ( Gon gasps )

217
00:11:00,928 --> 00:11:03,564
Meleoron: I sent them
to attack so I could see

218
00:11:03,597 --> 00:11:06,300
how much strength
you were working with,

219
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:08,435
and you saw how that went.

220
00:11:08,468 --> 00:11:10,904
Uh, but no need to feel bad.

221
00:11:10,938 --> 00:11:12,506
As it turns out,

222
00:11:12,539 --> 00:11:15,509
those bastards were killing
for fun behind my back.

223
00:11:15,542 --> 00:11:19,212
They’re not my soldiers
or my allies anymore.

224
00:11:19,246 --> 00:11:22,449
well, I guess
from their perspective,

225
00:11:22,482 --> 00:11:25,418
i’m the one who changed,
not them.

226
00:11:26,687 --> 00:11:29,223
Gon: About being your partner...

227
00:11:29,256 --> 00:11:32,226
i’m just not
the partner you want.

228
00:11:32,259 --> 00:11:35,395
Meleoron: You know
someone who’d be better?

229
00:11:35,429 --> 00:11:37,398
Gon: I sure do.

230
00:11:37,431 --> 00:11:38,732
I’ll contact him.

231
00:11:38,765 --> 00:11:40,734
Meleoron: Hold on.

232
00:11:40,767 --> 00:11:43,270
Right or wrong, I do trust you.

233
00:11:43,303 --> 00:11:46,807
And if you end up betraying me,
I won’t blame you,

234
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:48,675
and I won’t even
regret my decision,

235
00:11:48,709 --> 00:11:51,545
because I watched you,
and I spoke to you,

236
00:11:51,578 --> 00:11:54,748
and it was my choice
to trust you,

237
00:11:54,781 --> 00:11:57,884
but i’m not about to place
my trust in someone else

238
00:11:57,918 --> 00:11:59,453
just because you trust them.

239
00:11:59,486 --> 00:12:01,555
That’s not how
this is gonna work.

240
00:12:01,588 --> 00:12:02,956
That make sense to you?

241
00:12:02,990 --> 00:12:05,693
Gon: Mm-hmm. I get your point,
but still--

242
00:12:05,726 --> 00:12:08,963
meleoron: Hey, it’s my life
on the line here, right?

243
00:12:10,998 --> 00:12:15,035
Listen. My perfect plan’s
not invincible at all.

244
00:12:15,068 --> 00:12:17,771
It’s actually more vulnerable
than you might think.

245
00:12:17,804 --> 00:12:20,573
Nobody is aware of me
or my existence,

246
00:12:20,607 --> 00:12:23,577
but i’m still right there
in the same place.

247
00:12:23,610 --> 00:12:25,479
It isn’t like
i’ve gone anywhere.

248
00:12:25,512 --> 00:12:27,714
It’s just they
may not notice me,

249
00:12:27,748 --> 00:12:29,783
but their attacks
can still hit me.

250
00:12:29,816 --> 00:12:32,819
if an enemy knew
that they were in the same room

251
00:12:32,853 --> 00:12:35,689
as somebody with my ability,
what would they do then?

252
00:12:35,722 --> 00:12:38,959
They’d launch attacks
in every direction.

253
00:12:38,992 --> 00:12:40,694
( Gon gasps )
Yeah, you’re right.

254
00:12:40,727 --> 00:12:42,996
meleoron: If one
of those attacks hit me,

255
00:12:43,030 --> 00:12:45,533
even by dumb luck,
i’d be done for.

256
00:12:45,566 --> 00:12:48,736
hate to say it,
but when it comes to combat,

257
00:12:48,769 --> 00:12:50,704
i’m the weakest
chimera ant around.

258
00:12:50,737 --> 00:12:52,439
I’m basically a foot soldier.

259
00:12:52,472 --> 00:12:53,974
Forget the king.

260
00:12:54,007 --> 00:12:57,310
I couldn’t even survive a punch
from a squadron leader.

261
00:12:57,344 --> 00:13:01,715
If I just turn invisible,
I can be located with en.

262
00:13:01,748 --> 00:13:02,983
It’s already been tested,

263
00:13:03,016 --> 00:13:05,719
so the other squadron leaders
know it, too.

264
00:13:05,752 --> 00:13:09,522
I need my enemies to believe
that my power is weak.

265
00:13:09,556 --> 00:13:12,325
They need to think
just a little bit of en

266
00:13:12,359 --> 00:13:13,660
is enough to beat it.

267
00:13:13,694 --> 00:13:17,498
so the only way
this ability is invincible

268
00:13:17,531 --> 00:13:21,035
is if no one knows it exists
in the first place.

269
00:13:21,068 --> 00:13:23,003
But enough explaining.

270
00:13:23,036 --> 00:13:26,506
my point is that
I don’t want to reveal my power

271
00:13:26,540 --> 00:13:30,511
to anyone else, not even
if it’s someone you trust.

272
00:13:30,544 --> 00:13:32,446
You understand?

273
00:13:32,479 --> 00:13:35,015
Gon: Find out for yourself.

274
00:13:35,048 --> 00:13:36,049
Meleoron: Huh?

275
00:13:36,083 --> 00:13:37,751
Gon: I’ll call him over,

276
00:13:37,784 --> 00:13:39,919
but I won’t mention
that you’re here.

277
00:13:39,953 --> 00:13:41,755
- ( Cell phone beeps )
- Meleoron: Hey, wait.

278
00:13:41,788 --> 00:13:44,524
Gon: You can watch things
from a distance.

279
00:13:44,558 --> 00:13:45,726
( Phone line ringing )

280
00:13:45,759 --> 00:13:47,461
- Gon: Hi. It’s--
- knuckle: Hey!

281
00:13:47,494 --> 00:13:49,429
I’ve been waiting, idiot.

282
00:13:49,463 --> 00:13:52,466
You pulled a fast one.
where are you?

283
00:13:52,499 --> 00:13:56,069
i’ve got lots
of questions for you.

284
00:13:56,103 --> 00:14:00,007
The boss had to make a move
because of you two kids.

285
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:01,975
The original plan’s
been completely derailed,

286
00:14:02,009 --> 00:14:04,979
but I approve of what
you’re doing out there.

287
00:14:05,012 --> 00:14:06,614
( Gon gasps )

288
00:14:06,647 --> 00:14:08,449
Knov: We can’t just let

289
00:14:08,482 --> 00:14:11,385
five million innocent people
die like that.

290
00:14:11,418 --> 00:14:13,387
The boss already
used his ability

291
00:14:13,420 --> 00:14:14,922
to surround the capital.

292
00:14:14,955 --> 00:14:16,156
Gon: Really?

293
00:14:16,190 --> 00:14:18,626
knuckle: Yeah.
That should make it harder

294
00:14:18,659 --> 00:14:21,162
for neferpitou to use
their ability remotely,

295
00:14:21,195 --> 00:14:23,497
so they’re not going to be able

296
00:14:23,530 --> 00:14:25,799
to perform any kind
of long-distance sorting.

297
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:27,001
Gon: Right.

298
00:14:27,034 --> 00:14:29,670
Knuckle: However,
the boss and Mr. Knov

299
00:14:29,703 --> 00:14:33,006
will be expending all their
energy to delay neferpitou,

300
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:35,910
which means,
when the operation begins,

301
00:14:35,943 --> 00:14:38,179
they’re not gonna be
in any condition

302
00:14:38,212 --> 00:14:40,748
to take on the royal guards.

303
00:14:40,781 --> 00:14:42,116
( Gon sighs )

304
00:14:42,149 --> 00:14:45,419
Knuckle: We fully expect
that more citizens

305
00:14:45,452 --> 00:14:48,121
will gather in the capital
for the celebration.

306
00:14:48,155 --> 00:14:50,691
There might still be a massacre.

307
00:14:50,724 --> 00:14:53,860
the situation
hasn’t gotten any less grim.

308
00:14:56,897 --> 00:14:59,867
We can’t contact
the chairman anymore.

309
00:14:59,900 --> 00:15:03,470
he’s focusing and
honing his energy somewhere,

310
00:15:03,504 --> 00:15:05,673
waiting for zero hour.

311
00:15:05,706 --> 00:15:07,708
♪

312
00:15:11,712 --> 00:15:15,049
the four of us
need to make a choice.

313
00:15:15,082 --> 00:15:17,084
Do we summon reinforcements

314
00:15:17,117 --> 00:15:20,087
or face the three royal guards
all by ourselves?

315
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:21,722
( Gon groans )

316
00:15:21,755 --> 00:15:24,625
Knuckle: What does killua
think about it?

317
00:15:24,658 --> 00:15:25,959
Gon: He’s not here.

318
00:15:25,993 --> 00:15:28,963
Knuckle: Are you saying
that you two split up?

319
00:15:28,996 --> 00:15:33,133
oh, I get it.
He was doing all this himself.

320
00:15:33,167 --> 00:15:35,102
Can you call him?

321
00:15:35,135 --> 00:15:37,137
( Busy signal beeping )

322
00:15:39,740 --> 00:15:42,076
Gon: Sorry. He’s not picking up.

323
00:15:42,109 --> 00:15:43,877
His phone is off.

324
00:15:43,911 --> 00:15:46,914
Knuckle: That so? Well,
don’t give up. Keep trying.

325
00:15:46,947 --> 00:15:49,216
we should all
touch base real soon,

326
00:15:49,249 --> 00:15:51,685
- and the sooner, the better.
- Gon: Yeah.

327
00:15:51,718 --> 00:15:53,753
Knuckle: We need to find
a halfway point for us

328
00:15:53,787 --> 00:15:55,222
where we can meet up
when we can.

329
00:15:55,255 --> 00:15:56,723
Shoot: Mm.

330
00:15:56,757 --> 00:15:59,727
Knuckle: Here. Mandai city.

331
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:01,829
Gon: Right. Got it.

332
00:16:01,862 --> 00:16:03,831
( Hangs up )

333
00:16:09,903 --> 00:16:11,905
♪

334
00:16:19,213 --> 00:16:20,247
King: Checkmate.

335
00:16:22,316 --> 00:16:24,051
You’re finished.

336
00:16:24,084 --> 00:16:26,086
( Man stammering )

337
00:16:27,921 --> 00:16:31,057
King: Now, why didn’t
you concede defeat?

338
00:16:33,093 --> 00:16:34,094
Man: Uh...

339
00:16:35,796 --> 00:16:37,865
( Wincing )

340
00:16:37,898 --> 00:16:41,101
king: Do not
make me repeat myself.

341
00:16:41,134 --> 00:16:44,270
The match was decided
22 moves ago.

342
00:16:44,304 --> 00:16:47,073
so then tell me
why you didn’t concede.

343
00:16:47,107 --> 00:16:50,577
Did you actually think
that I would make a mistake?

344
00:16:50,611 --> 00:16:53,180
( Man gasping )

345
00:17:05,259 --> 00:17:06,293
( Yelps )

346
00:17:06,326 --> 00:17:08,728
King: The fool.

347
00:17:10,097 --> 00:17:13,233
Shaiapouf: Next we have
the national go champion.

348
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:15,636
King: Hand over the rule book.

349
00:17:18,672 --> 00:17:22,242
Shaiapouf: It looks simple,
but it’s a very complex game.

350
00:17:22,276 --> 00:17:27,148
It may take even more time
to learn than shogi.

351
00:17:27,181 --> 00:17:29,183
♪

352
00:17:39,293 --> 00:17:42,763
Champion: Please, let me go!
What do you want?!

353
00:17:42,796 --> 00:17:46,366
Someone, anyone, help me!

354
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,402
( Groans )

355
00:17:50,003 --> 00:17:51,104
My glasses.

356
00:17:51,138 --> 00:17:52,373
Shaiapouf: Silence.

357
00:17:52,406 --> 00:17:55,209
You are in the presence
of the king.

358
00:18:00,047 --> 00:18:02,616
( Champion gasping )

359
00:18:02,649 --> 00:18:05,152
King: The choice is yours.

360
00:18:05,185 --> 00:18:08,355
You will either
sit across from me,

361
00:18:08,388 --> 00:18:11,658
or you will die.

362
00:18:11,692 --> 00:18:13,394
( Game piece clatters )

363
00:18:17,097 --> 00:18:19,700
Shaiapouf: 5 1/2 points.

364
00:18:19,733 --> 00:18:20,867
The king wins.

365
00:18:20,901 --> 00:18:24,671
champion:
It only took him 10 games?

366
00:18:24,705 --> 00:18:26,974
I’m just tired, that’s all.

367
00:18:27,007 --> 00:18:28,242
That’s why I lost.

368
00:18:28,275 --> 00:18:30,244
I might have a slight fever.

369
00:18:30,277 --> 00:18:32,379
I’m really dizzy and weak.

370
00:18:32,412 --> 00:18:36,750
King: Take eight hours
and medicine.

371
00:18:36,783 --> 00:18:39,386
I want you in top condition.

372
00:18:39,419 --> 00:18:44,057
Lose again, and I won’t be
interested in your excuses,

373
00:18:44,091 --> 00:18:46,994
so rest like you mean it.

374
00:18:51,131 --> 00:18:54,334
Shaiapouf: I’m impressed
by how quickly you learn.

375
00:18:54,368 --> 00:18:56,070
these games
are quite difficult.

376
00:18:56,103 --> 00:18:58,072
I’m shocked that it took you

377
00:18:58,105 --> 00:19:00,841
less than half the time
it took to learn shogi.

378
00:19:00,874 --> 00:19:03,710
king: I just learned
the trick to it. That was all.

379
00:19:03,744 --> 00:19:09,383
chess, go, shogi,
the rules may be different,

380
00:19:09,416 --> 00:19:11,685
but every first-rate player

381
00:19:11,718 --> 00:19:14,321
has a certain rhythm
to his play.

382
00:19:14,354 --> 00:19:17,190
The key is to disrupt
their rhythm

383
00:19:17,224 --> 00:19:19,126
and therefore their game.

384
00:19:19,159 --> 00:19:22,729
As soon as you learn the basics,
you can deduce their rhythm...

385
00:19:22,763 --> 00:19:24,865
♪

386
00:19:24,898 --> 00:19:28,335
And once you know their rhythm,
disrupting it is easy.

387
00:19:28,368 --> 00:19:30,804
shaiapouf:
A psychological approach

388
00:19:30,838 --> 00:19:32,940
that would apply
to any contest.

389
00:19:32,973 --> 00:19:35,375
So now that you’ve learned this,

390
00:19:35,409 --> 00:19:38,379
I fail to see the benefit
of further games.

391
00:19:38,412 --> 00:19:41,282
I believe they will
only serve to bore you.

392
00:19:41,315 --> 00:19:42,283
King: Mm.

393
00:19:42,316 --> 00:19:45,286
What else remains?

394
00:19:45,319 --> 00:19:49,056
Shaiapouf: Just one more game
is played here professionally.

395
00:19:49,089 --> 00:19:51,792
It’s a board game
that they call gungi.

396
00:19:51,825 --> 00:19:53,927
King: What is that?

397
00:19:53,961 --> 00:19:56,764
Shaiapouf: Seems the game
began in east gorteau,

398
00:19:56,797 --> 00:20:00,134
and nearly all the citizens
there know how to play it.

399
00:20:00,167 --> 00:20:02,169
King: Give me the rule book.

400
00:20:05,772 --> 00:20:07,374
shaiapouf:
The goal is to checkmate

401
00:20:07,407 --> 00:20:09,242
your opponent’s king,
as in chess.

402
00:20:10,878 --> 00:20:14,281
However, pieces can be
stacked up to three high,

403
00:20:14,314 --> 00:20:17,851
and the opening formation
of pieces is variable.

404
00:20:17,885 --> 00:20:21,021
it requires
three-dimensional thinking,

405
00:20:21,054 --> 00:20:22,789
making it somewhat different

406
00:20:22,823 --> 00:20:24,858
from other board games
of this nature.

407
00:20:24,892 --> 00:20:27,361
World tournaments have
been held around the globe

408
00:20:27,394 --> 00:20:29,329
each of the last 15 years,

409
00:20:29,363 --> 00:20:33,067
and, in all that time,
east gorteau has yet to lose.

410
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:35,469
they are now
on their third representative,

411
00:20:35,502 --> 00:20:37,871
who is a five-time
reigning champion.

412
00:20:37,905 --> 00:20:39,073
King: Hmm.

413
00:20:39,106 --> 00:20:41,275
So then if I defeat
this champion,

414
00:20:41,308 --> 00:20:43,076
i’ll be the best in the world?

415
00:20:43,110 --> 00:20:46,880
A fitting end to this diversion.

416
00:20:46,914 --> 00:20:48,382
Call them.

417
00:20:55,122 --> 00:20:57,124
(Cane tapping)

418
00:21:10,170 --> 00:21:13,106
Narrator: Six days left
until the sorting.

419
00:21:13,140 --> 00:21:17,177
A young girl appears who will
shape the fate of the king.

420
00:21:17,211 --> 00:21:19,113
But in what way, exactly...

421
00:21:19,146 --> 00:21:22,149
He has no idea at all.

422
00:21:22,182 --> 00:21:25,152
♪

423
00:21:25,185 --> 00:21:27,187
( Singing in Japanese )

